#1 Metastatic colon cancer with known liver metastasis
The patient will receive cycle four of FOLFOX plus Avastin with omission of 5-FU bolus on the 6th of May.  She will return again on the 20th of May for her fifth cycle of chemotherapy.  She will be seen again by Dr. Mefford on the 3rd of June prior to her sixth cycle of treatment.  She seems to be responding both by CEA and radiologically and is tolerating the treatment well.  She uses Imodium for any slight diarrhea she experiences.
#2 History of neutropenia, chemotherapy-related
We are omitting bolus 5-FU
#3 Elevated blood pressure
The patient's blood pressure is elevated today.  This will need to be continuously monitored as she is on Avastin and also takes metoprolol and hydrochlorothiazide.
#4 Thyroid nodules seen on CT-scan
This should be noted, and we will add-on thyroid function studies at this time, but we will not pursue an ultrasound given her metastatic colon cancer and the fact that she is undergoing chemotherapy at this time.
#5 Colon cancer at young-onset age
The patient has had MSI testing which showed MSI low and no evidence of HNPCC.  She has three children, and it was recommended that they begin screening colonoscopies at the age of 30.  I also offered her a medical genetics consultation as there are some other possibilities that could be explored such as MYH-associated polyposis or FAP.  She will decide if she would like to meet with Medical Genetics and let us know.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

